result.name: Star of Canton Restaurant

reviews.text: Food quality and service have declined in the past couple of years. The wonton and chicken soup dish was off. The manager didn't charge for the dish. Will not select this restaurant next time.

They take advantage of westerners when it comes to tip. I was taking money to pay and there is already 10% service charge and they speak in perfect English asking for tip. I was only taking the money back to our table and said we would leave a tip. This caused a stir at our table since the people I was having a meal with said they are doing that because you're a Westerner. Food was good though, but what a way to end the meal. Staff is more concerned about a few HKD (which they would have gotten) than repeat business.
Poor service, substandard food and terribly presented, please don’t come to waste time and money
Ok restaurant. Very crowded and we were only given a table for 8 to fit 12 people. Food is ok, some is good some stuff is a bit chewy. Feels a bit under staffed.
Good food cheap price
